---
title: "CLI reference"
---

The `{{ site_name }}-cli` binary provides direct shell access to the
{{ site_display_name }} API.  Every search, count, and snippet operation
is available without writing code.

```bash
{{ site_name }}-cli --help
```

---

## Global flags

| Flag | Description |
|---|---|
| `--url` | Print the API URL instead of making a request |
| `--size N` | Number of results to return (default: `10`) |
| `--page N` | Page number, 1-based (default: `1`) |
| `--sort FIELD:ORDER` | Sort field and direction, e.g. `genome_size:desc` |
| `--include-estimates` | Include estimated values (default: true) |
| `--taxonomy NAME` | Taxonomy to use, e.g. `ncbi` (default: `ncbi`) |
| `--format FORMAT` | Output format: `tsv`, `csv`, `json` (default: `tsv`) |
| `--all` | Fetch every matching record via cursor-based pagination. Output is always JSON. |
| `--max-results N` | Cap the total records fetched when `--all` is set. |

---

## Per-index subcommands

{% for index in indexes %}
### `{{ site_name }}-cli {{ index.name }}`

```
{{ site_name }}-cli {{ index.name }} <COMMAND> [OPTIONS]
```

**Commands**: `count`, `search`, `record`, `summary`, `report`, `snippet`

#### `count`

```bash
# How many {{ index.name }} records match?
{{ site_name }}-cli {{ index.name }} count {% if loop.first %}--taxon Mammalia --taxon-filter tree --rank species{% endif %}

```

#### `search`

```bash
{{ site_name }}-cli {{ index.name }} search \{% if loop.first %}
  --taxon Mammalia --taxon-filter tree \
  --rank species \
  --fields genome_size,assembly_level \
  --sort genome_size:desc \
  --size 20{% endif %}

```

#### `snippet`

Generate a code snippet for this query in the language of your choice:

```bash
{{ site_name }}-cli {{ index.name }} snippet \{% if loop.first %}
  --taxon Mammalia --taxon-filter tree \
  --fields genome_size \
  --lang python{% endif %}

```

#### `record`

```bash
{{ site_name }}-cli {{ index.name }} record GCA_000001405.15{% if loop.first %} --format json{% endif %}

```

#### `summary`

```bash
{{ site_name }}-cli {{ index.name }} summary GCA_000001405.15{% if loop.first %} --fields genome_size,assembly_level{% endif %}

```

#### `report`

```bash
{{ site_name }}-cli {{ index.name }} report histogram{% if loop.first %} \
  --taxon Mammalia --taxon-filter tree \
  --x genome_size --rank species{% endif %}

```

{% endfor %}

## Batch subcommands

### `{{ site_name }}-cli search-batch`

Execute multiple searches defined in a JSON or YAML file:

```bash
{{ site_name }}-cli search-batch queries.json --format json
```

Each entry in `queries.json` is a query object with the same flags as `search`.
Results are returned as a JSON array, one element per query.

### `{{ site_name }}-cli count-batch`

Get hit counts for multiple queries in a single request:

```bash
{{ site_name }}-cli count-batch queries.json
```

---

## Filter syntax

### Taxon filters

```
--taxon NAME [--taxon-filter {name|tree|lineage}]
```

- `name` (default) â€” match taxa by exact or fuzzy name
- `tree` â€” include the entire subtree rooted at `NAME`
- `lineage` â€” include only taxa that have `NAME` in their lineage

Prefix with `!` to exclude:

```bash
--taxon Mammalia --taxon Rodentia!
# or
--taxon "Mammalia,!Rodentia"
```

### Attribute filters

```
--filter "FIELD OPERATOR VALUE"
```

| Example | Meaning |
|---|---|
| `"genome_size >= 1G"` | Genome size at least 1 gigabyte |
| `"assembly_level eq chromosome"` | Chromosome-level assemblies only |
| `"busco_completeness exists"` | Field must be present |
| `"c_value missing"` | Field must be absent |

Size suffixes `G`, `M`, `K` are accepted for numeric byte fields.

Source modifiers restrict to specific provenance:

```bash
--filter "genome_size >= 1G direct"
```

### Assembly / sample filters

```
--assembly GCA_XXXXXXXXX.N
--sample SAMXXXXXXXX
```

---

## Output formats

### TSV (default)

```bash
{{ site_name }}-cli taxon search --taxon Mammalia --fields genome_size
# scientific_name  taxon_rank  genome_size  genome_size_source
# Homo sapiens     species     3100000000   direct
```

### JSON

```bash
{{ site_name }}-cli taxon search --taxon Mammalia --fields genome_size --format json
```

### URL only

Print the query URL without fetching data â€” useful for debugging or calling
from other tools:

```bash
{{ site_name }}-cli taxon search --taxon Mammalia --fields genome_size --url
# https://{{ api_base | trim_start_matches(pat="https://") }}/{{ api_version }}/search?...
```

---

## Examples

### Top 10 largest mammal genomes

```bash
{{ site_name }}-cli taxon search \
  --taxon Mammalia --taxon-filter tree \
  --rank species \
  --fields genome_size \
  --sort genome_size:desc \
  --size 10
```

### Count insects with busco scores

```bash
{{ site_name }}-cli taxon count \
  --taxon Insecta --taxon-filter tree \
  --rank species \
  --filter "busco_completeness exists"
```

### Export all results to CSV

```bash
{{ site_name }}-cli taxon search \
  --taxon Vertebrata --taxon-filter tree \
  --fields genome_size,assembly_level,busco_completeness \
  --size 10000 \
  --format csv > vertebrate_genomes.csv
```

### Fetch all matching records (pagination)

Use `--all` to retrieve every page automatically.  Output is always JSON and
progress is written to stderr so you can pipe stdout:

```bash
{{ site_name }}-cli taxon search \
  --taxon Mammalia --taxon-filter tree \
  --rank species \
  --fields genome_size \
  --all > mammalia_species.json

# Cap at 5 000 records
{{ site_name }}-cli taxon search \
  --taxon Mammalia --taxon-filter tree \
  --rank species \
  --fields genome_size \
  --all --max-results 5000 > mammalia_species.json
```
